title: SOLD: Joe Doyle partial NATL error - the Poor Mans Doyle NATL
author: jggames

posts.post_title: SOLD: Joe Doyle partial NATL error - the Poor Mans Doyle NATL
posts.post_content:
Selling this guy go for what I paid earlier this year. $230 FF or add the fee for goods. 

Many here are probably aware of this card, but short story goes…TedZ along with a few others noticed a small printers mark where the “N” in Nat’l should be on some Piedmont 350s. The actual Doyle error only occurs on Pied350s. While this printers mark does show up on other backs, I think it’s cool to imagine this P350 being printed with the same plate as the Doyle error (with just 99% of the error removed).

See thread here: [URL="https://www.net54baseball.com/showthread.php?t=87066&highlight=slow+joe+doyle"]https://www.net54baseball.com/showthread.php?t=87066&highlight=slow+joe+doyle[/URL]
